11. At what level is the arcuate line located?
That's right!  The inferior border of the posterior lamina is identifiable as the arcuate line. It locates midway between the umbilicus and the pubic crest.
That is incorrect. Click here      to learn the answer, then come back to try again.

Along the lower ¼ of the rectus abdominis, all three aponeurotic layers derived from the three flat muscles pass anterior to the rectus abdominis, leaving the posterior surface of the rectus abdominis in contact with the transversalis fascia.  
The transition between these two structural arrangements of the rectus sheath is abrupt. It occurs roughly at the halfway point between the umbilicus and the pubic crest, where the inferior border of the posterior lamina is identifiable as the arcuate line.
A. THE RECTUS SHEATH ABOVE THE ARCUATE LINE
B. THE RECTUS SHEATH BELOW THE ARCUATE LINE
